The paper presents an intelligent assistant designed for E-commerce, which involves natural language processing and question answering techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of AI techniques, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. The system also incorporates context to QA, which is related to information retrieval, indicating cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a possible sub-category. The system's ability to support multi-round interaction and its focus on customer service suggest cs.LG (Learning) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the real-world application of the system, which involves user interaction and experience, indicating cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as a potential sub-category.
